{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3bd402cb-eabb-4643-802b-3a70bcf4f92e","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **natively**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed and can be removed.\n\nYou still need `EnableMSTestRunner` to make the test project an MTP executable. Here's the cleanup:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_017BpC1iTwBb8iEwgxDDtthe","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_011hCfCgiys6XTETiownBmEs","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-401a3fab5465441caa5f4f7ac48534f7/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-401a3fab5465441caa5f4f7ac48534f7/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"ba07ce43-353e-4918-bde2-9c1546974360","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about MTP support. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. This property was needed in .NET 9 and earlier to opt into MTP support via `dotnet test`, but in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses MTP by default.\n\nSo the user can remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` from their project file. The `EnableMSTestRunner` property is still needed to enable the MSTest runner (which makes the test project an executable that uses MTP).\n\n\nNow I'll show them the updated project file with the unnecessary property removed.","outputTokens":478,"requestId":"982E:15489A:18F13B:206C69:69FFD8BF"},"id":"5a77d71e-7ba0-4b83-a6c3-72dd326f1fda","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:00:55.032Z","parentId":"d1aa6af7-e65f-475c-8057-d0b5c1e42031"}
