{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"05d9daba-c2b2-479a-ac52-1b422b322c51","content":"**Summary:**\n\n- **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`** — **remove it**. It was a .NET 9 bridge property to make `dotnet test` talk to MTP. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` speaks MTP natively.\n- **`EnableMSTestRunner`** — **keep it**. This makes your test project build as an MTP executable, which is still required.\n- **`OutputType Exe`** — **keep it**. Required by the MSTest runner.\n\nJust run `dotnet test` as usual — it will use the new MTP-native pipeline automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ba07ce43-353e-4918-bde2-9c1546974360","outputTokens":148,"requestId":"982A:2C5C9E:184950:1FD605:69FFD8C8"},"id":"0872bb13-b77d-47fe-88a1-aaad51a6c809","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:01:02.244Z","parentId":"34c6ee3e-9d9f-4415-b655-ee6471df1c76"}
